description: Core conventions for the AI Content Moderation Platform
globs: ["**/*.ts", "**/*.tsx"]
---

# Stack
- Backend: NestJS + TypeScript, Mongoose. Frontend: Next.js App Router + TypeScript, TanStack Query.
- Follow the schemas and endpoint contracts in PROJECT_PLAN.md exactly. Do not invent additional fields
  or rename collections without flagging it first.

# Before importing anything
- Never assume a package is installed based on training data. Run `npm list <package>` in the relevant
  workspace first. If it's not there, install it explicitly and say so.

# Interface-first
- When adding a new feature, write the TypeScript interfaces/DTOs and the Mongoose schema first, in
  isolation, before touching any service or controller logic. Show me that before continuing.

# Boundaries
- Never modify .env, docker-compose.yml, or package.json without calling it out explicitly first.
- Never commit or push. I review and commit myself.
- If you're not sure whether something matches PROJECT_PLAN.md section 3 (Non-Negotiable Design
  Decisions), stop and ask rather than guessing.

# Style
- Be concise. Don't explain standard NestJS/Next.js patterns I already know. Focus only on what's
  actually new or non-obvious in a given change.